    "body": "Didn't realize that you were mixing plot types. Bar and line will have different ticks in general since bar will plot every label. I guess you could try reversing the order?\n\n``` python\nIn [10]: ax = df.Metric2.unstack([-1,-2]).plot()\nIn [11]: ax.set(xticks=[])\nOut[11]: [[]]\nIn [13]: df.Metric1.unstack([-1,-2]).plot(kind='bar', ax=ax)\nOut[13]: <matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x10b6b1a20>\n```\n\nYou're probably better off doing this all in matplotlib though. Once you start needing custom stuff the higher-level pandas API breaks down.\n"
